SUMMARY:Acadia Nat’l Park/Partial Solar Eclipse/Perseids Meteor Shower E
 vent
DESCRIPTION:Triangle Hiking and Outdoors Group\nCome and be a part of one 
 of THOG’s most ambitious trips. This summer adventure in Maine includes 
 Acadia National Park and Bar Harbor\, as well as two amazing celestial eve
 nts- A partial Solar Eclipse and the Perseids Meteor Shower.\nThis excitin
 g road trip event will be slightly different from other THOG events. We wi
 ll be partnering with Wanderful Journeys\, a local travel club that hosts 
 trips to various destinations. I decided to team up with them so it would 
 provide us with another layer of resources for planning\, as well as to en
 hance the trip experience.\n**See RSVP requirements below before you regis
 ter**.\n\n**Highlights of our weeklong trip will include:**\n-Hikes in Aca
 dia National Park such as Precipice Trail and Beehive Trail\n-Thunder Hole
 \n-Jordan Pond\n-Maine Lobster :)\n-Lighthouses in Maine\n-Viewing the par
 tial Solar Eclipse\n-Watching the Perseids Meteor Shower (up to 100 per ho
 ur)\n-Exploring Bar Harbor\n-Bar Island Trail hike- a trail that appears o
 nly during low tide\n-Exclusive Swag options for trip participants\n\n**He
 re is a brief overview of our itinerary on this trip** which is subject to
  change depending on weather and/or other factors:\n8/9- Carpools will mee
 t in a central location in the triangle and begin Day 1 of our trip with a
 n overnight stop at a hotel in NJ\n8/10- Continue our trip with a featured
  stop along the way at Portland Head Light then arrive at Acadia Nat'l Par
 k/Bar Harbor for either camping or hotel stay\n8/11- Sunrise at Cadillac M
 ountain\, hiking choices in Acadia and other activities then dinner at cam
 p or in Bar Harbor\n8/12- Solar Eclipse Day Activities: Sunrise and hike a
 t Otter Point\, Watch partial Solar Eclipse nearby\, Explore Bar Harbor\, 
 Sunset at Bass Harbor Head Lighthouse\n8/13- Activities: Bar Island Trail 
 hike\, Thunder Hole\, Jordan Pond\n8/14- Head back to NJ to our hotel with
  a featured stop along the way.\n8/15- Continue our trip back home with a 
 featured stop along the way.\nAll participants will be required to pay a $
 100 deposit to secure their spot on this trip.\n**Accommodations overview:
 ** Everyone will be staying at a designated hotel in NJ going to Maine and
  returning from Maine.\nIn Maine\, you will have two stay options:\n-desig
 nated Group Campsites (4 nights) that has modern bathrooms\; paid showers 
 are located nearby\n-designated hotel in Bar Harbor (4 nights) two beds pe
 r room\nIf you choose the hotel stay in Maine\, it is crucial that you sub
 mit your deposit as soon as you RSVP (see rsvp requirements below) to secu
 re your hotel spot due to limited room availability. Roommate info/rules w
 ill also be in a link that will be sent to all who RSVP.\n**important RSVP
  requirements:**\n\n1. You will be asked a three-part question as you are 
 RSVPing for this event. Please answer completely!\n2. After you RSVP to th
 is trip\, you will be sent a **link to your email** **address** that will 
 have questions you need to answer as well as a link to pay your **$100 dep
 osit (required for every trip participant)**. Links will have all the info
 rmation about the trip\, total costs per person\, rules on how the deposit
  works\, itinerary\, trip expectations\, and swag information.\nYour spot 
 on this trip will not be guaranteed until the deposit is paid.\n\nWe look 
 forward to having you be a part of this adventure!\nIf you have any questi
 ons\, please send me (Larredo) a meetup message or comment below if it is 
 something that could benefit the group. Thanks!\nSee you all soon!\nLarred
 o and Geniece\n\nTRIP PARTICIPANT WAIVER OF LIABILITY I fully realize that
  this activity involves a risk of personal injury\, property damage\, or l
 oss of my person or property. I hereby for myself\, my heirs\, executors a
 nd administrators\, and same for persons with whom are in my party\, waive
  and release any claims or rights against Triangle Hiking & Outdoors Group
  (THOG)\, all of its owners and coordinators for any and all injury\, dama
 ges or loss to my person or property incurred during this activity. I also
  understand that THOG organizers are not required\, nor should it be assum
 ed that they are CPR/First Aid/Wilderness Survival Certified and I am resp
 onsible for my own personal safety.
